Microsoft SQL Server - relational database management system (DBMS) developed by Microsoft. The main query language used - Transact-SQL, created by Microsoft and Sybase. Transact-SQL is an implementation of ANSI / ISO standard Structured Query Language (SQL) extensions. Used to work with small and medium-sized databases to large enterprise database. MS SQL Server 2014 - the new relational database management system, available in the same versions as the previous version of 2012 - Standard, Business Intelligence (BI) and Enterprise, which differ in the number of supported processor cores, the rules work in virtualized mode, the presence of security functions / fault tolerance, as well as the main problem to be solved (using as a server transaction processing or analytical applications).
